projects.description:
This 1,698,135 Euros worth Dutch Government funded project is implemented together with Maastricht School of Management in Egypt, aiming to support and increase capacity of the Training Sector Water Resources and Irrigation, to become "an effective regional center capable of facilitating learning and development in water management within and outside of Egypt". Hamdard was project leader from UNESCO-IHE side.

The project objectives are two folded:

A- Institutional development and strengthening the support structure
       - Training for managerial staff, exposure visit, developing Quality Assurance System, establishing E-learning environment, Gender sensitive strategy;

B- Curriculum renewal and the introduction of Modern Learning Techniques
       - Introduction and training on Modern Learning Techniques, curriculum development for technical training, training for senior management, management group and engineering group;

profile_positions.description:
Hamdard's main responsibilities as Environmental Consultant were to support the Environmental Safeguards portfolio SASDN unit in Afghanistan, particularly in the World Bank funded projects such as Emergency Irrigation Rehabilitation Project , Rural Water and Sanitation Project, National Emergency Rural Access Project, National Solidarity Project together with the Environmental Specialist and in close consultation with relevant Task Team Leaders of the projects.  Hamdard  provided environmental support and worked with the SASDN unit as well as other sectors within the South Asia Sustainable Development Department on relevant activities in Afghanistan.   

Activities included, but are not limited, to the following:

- Assist clients with the application of Bank environmental safeguard policies;

- Participate with the Bank Task Teams in project supervision missions and contribute to Aide Memoires about the status and implementation of the Bank’s safeguards policies, effectiveness of the Environmental Management Framework in the  respective projects;

- Assist in the preparation of the TORs for conducting EAs, review of EA/EMF documents carried out by the client, and review compliance with Bank safeguard policies and quality acceptable to the Bank;

- Review all environmental screening associated with the EA process, including IEE, EIA, and EMP carried out by the client for each of the projects and provide feedback;

- Support on environment aspects of projects to Bank missions and task teams through out the project cycle, including preparation, pre-appraisal, appraisal, negotiations, and supervision, including by contributions to PADs, PCNs, etc. 

- Provide support to the Environment Specialist and the Task Team Leader on preparation for training client agencies’ staff on Environmental Safeguards and Environmental Management issues in the above mentioned WB funded projects;
